 of the camp and reassemble it differently. Drawing on fieldwork in Zaatari camp, Ayham Dalal offers a unique architectural insight into dwelling as a complex human phenomenon situated at heart of our precarious modern living.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 4aDwelling. 4aJordan. 4aRefugees. 4aSyria. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh  aArchitecture.  aDwelling.  aFleeing.  aGeography.  aJordan.  aRefugee Studies.  aRefugees.  aSpace.  aSyria.  aUrban Planning.  aUrban Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z978311076731508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022z97831107685100 cprintz978383765838540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839458389?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839458389zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839458389/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076731-5 transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-076851-0 transcript English Fro